==Translingual==
===Etymology===
Probably from Etruscan '''[[𐌅]]''' (like Greek '''[[Ϝ]]''', '''[[ϝ]]''' and Latin '''[[F]]'''), from the Phoenician character [[waw]].

===Letter===
'''ᚠ'''

#A letter of the [[Runic]] alphabet, representing /f/ and associated with [[wealth]].

===Names===
*Old Norse: [[fé]]
*Old English: [[feoh]]

